ce:section.ce:para:
Based on the above considerations, here, we successfully synthesized N-GQDs modified mesoporous SnO2 hierarchical hollow cubes (NG/Snx
                     ) and studied their NO2 sensing performance. The results show that the optimal NG/Snx
                      sensor exhibits high response, fast response/recovery speed, good selectivity, repeatability, and impressive long-term stability for NO2 gas at a low working temperature of 130 °C. Furthermore, the optimal sensor has outstanding detection ability (Rg/Ra = 25.3) for low concentration NO2 (100 ppb). The enhanced NO2 sensing performance and the corresponding sensing mechanism are discussed.
